quran[53]{c,v,t}:
  51,31,"He said, \"What is your errand then, O Messengers"
  51,32,"They said, \"Surely we are sent to a guilty people"
  51,33,That we may send down upon them stone of clay (or brimstones)
  51,34,Sent forth from your Lord for the extravagant (those who transgress beyond bounds)
  51,35,Then We brought forth such believers as were therein
  51,36,But We found not therein but one house of those who had Surrendered (Muslims)
  51,37,And We left therein a sign for those who fear the grievous penalty
  51,38,And in Moses (was another sign). When We sent him to Pharaoh with clear authority
  51,39,"But he turned away with his forces and said, \"A sorcerer or a mad man"
  51,40,So We seized him and his hosts and hurled them into the sea and his was the blame
  51,41,And in A´ad (was another sign). When We sent upon them the destructive wind
  51,42,"It spared naught on which it blew, but made it like dust"
  51,43,"And in Thamud (was another sign). When it was said to them, \"Enjoy yourselves for a while"
  51,44,"But they revolted against the commandment of their Lord, so the rumbling (thunderbolt or stunning noise of an earthquake) overtook them while they looked"
  51,45,"And they were not able to rise up, nor could they defend themselves"
  51,46,"And the people of Noah (were also a sign) before that, surely they were a transgressing people"
  51,47,"And the heaven, We raised it high with power, and it is We that expand the vastness of space (or We are the expanders of it)"
  51,48,"And the earth, We have spread it out; how gracious was the Spreader thereof"
  51,49,"And of all things have We created pairs, that you may reflect (or receive instruction)"
  51,50,"Therefore flee unto Allah, surely I am a plain Warner to you from Him"
  51,51,"And set not up with Allah another God: surely I am a plain Warner to you from Him"
  51,52,"Thus there did not come to those before them a messenger but they said, \"(He is) A sorcerer or a mad man"
  51,53,Is this the legacy (or tradition) they have transmitted to each other? Nay! They are a people extravagant (transgressing beyond bounds)
  51,54,Then turn your back upon them for you are not to blame
  51,55,"And continue to teach (or remind), for surely the reminder profits the believers"
  51,56,And I have not created the jinn and mankind except to worship (serve) Me
  51,57,"No sustenance do I require from them, nor do I require that they should feed Me"
  51,58,"Surely it is Allah Who is the Bestower of sustenance, the Lord of Power, the ever Steadfast"
  51,59,"And lo! Those who do wrong shall have a portion like the portion of those of earlier generations, therefore let them not ask Me to hasten"
  51,60,Woe to those who disbelieve because of their Day which they are promised
  52,1,(I swear) By the Mount
  52,2,By a Decree inscribed
  52,3,"On a fine parchment, unrolled"
  52,4,And the much visited House
  52,5,And the canopy exalted
  52,6,And the swollen sea
  52,7,Most surely the doom of your Lord will come to pass
  52,8,There shall be none to avert it
  52,9,On the day when the heaven shall heave with awful commotion
  52,10,And the mountains shall move with awful movement
  52,11,Then woe on that Day unto the deniers (of the truth)
  52,12,Those who sport in vain discourses
  52,13,The Day on which they shall be driven irresistibly to the Fire of Hell
  52,14,This is the Fire which you used to deny
  52,15,"Is it magic then, or do you not see"
  52,16,"Burn you therein, and whether you bear it patiently or not, it makes no difference; you shall be requited only what you did"
  52,17,Surely those who guard (against evil) shall be in Gardens of Bliss
  52,18,"Rejoicing because of what their Lord gave them, and their Lord saved them from the punishment of the burning Fire"
  52,19,Eat and drink with profit and health because of what you did
  52,20,"Reclining on thrones set in ranks, and We will unite them to large-eyed beautiful ones (Houri)"
  52,21,"And as for those who believe and whose offspring follow them in faith, We will unite with them their offspring and We will not deprive them of naught of their work; each individual is a pledge for his own deeds"
  52,22,And We will provide them with fruit and flesh such as they desire
  52,23,They shall pass from one to another a cup wherein there shall be nothing vain nor any sin